lots of stops || it took me a fortnight and a fortune || in barcelona i stopped | looking at paintings and the awesome work of antoni gaudi || alabaster in the house | just brilliant craft || Gothic art is imperfect, it means to solve; it is the style of the compass, the formula of industrial repetition. Its stability is based on the permanent propping of abutments: it is a defective body that holds with support… gothic works produce maximum emotion when they are mutilated, covered with ivy and illuminated by the moon.[19] antoni gaudi barcelona spain [wiki] ac click link
